148
00:14:49,723 --> 00:14:51,807
- It was horrible.

149
00:14:51,809 --> 00:14:54,601
There was a girl there!

150
00:14:54,603 --> 00:14:56,645
It was a demon, it was a demon!

151
00:14:56,647 --> 00:14:57,478
- Come on now.

152
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,980
You're just trying to get us

153
00:14:58,982 --> 00:14:59,942
in the mood for some ghost
stories.

154
00:15:00,901 --> 00:15:03,819
- No, no, it really happened!

155
00:15:03,821 --> 00:15:05,989
- Maybe it was an apparition?

156
00:15:06,949 --> 00:15:07,948
- Uh-uh.

157
00:15:07,950 --> 00:15:10,659
Sounds like someone found the
shine and it had a good sip.

158
00:15:11,995 --> 00:15:14,329
- Maybe we should just
play a game or something?

159
00:15:14,331 --> 00:15:16,540
- This isn't time for charades!

160
00:15:16,542 --> 00:15:19,920
We need to tear this place up
for clues.

161
00:15:20,963 --> 00:15:23,964
- There's no way we could
read through all the letters.

162
00:15:46,655 --> 00:15:49,700
- Who do you think they are?
- Victims.

163
00:15:53,411 --> 00:15:55,288
- Lori, that's not funny!

164
00:15:59,543 --> 00:16:00,375
Who are you calling?

165
00:16:00,377 --> 00:16:01,920
- My boyfriend, Braddock.

166
00:16:02,963 --> 00:16:05,005
- Boyfriend? That's a laugh.

167
00:16:05,007 --> 00:16:06,214
- You've just never met him.

168
00:16:06,216 --> 00:16:07,465
He's a dream.

169
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:09,425
Wish he was here right now.

170
00:16:09,427 --> 00:16:11,011
